#### **1B: Create ItemSetting<T> System**

```java
// Create: src/main/java/.../config/ItemSetting.java

@ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public abstract class ItemSetting<T> {
    private final String key;
    private final T defaultValue;
    protected T value;

    public ItemSetting(@Nonnull String key, @Nonnull T defaultValue) {
        Validate.notNull(key, "'key' cannot be null!");
        Validate.notNull(defaultValue, "'defaultValue' cannot be null!");
        this.key = key;
        this.defaultValue = defaultValue;
        this.value = defaultValue;
    }

    // Override this to add validation
    public boolean validateInput(@Nonnull T input) {
        return input != null;
    }

    public void update(@Nonnull T newValue) {
        Validate.notNull(newValue, "'newValue' cannot be null!");
        if (validateInput(newValue)) {
            this.value = newValue;
            onUpdate(newValue);
        } else {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(
                "Invalid value for setting '" + key + "': " + newValue
            );
        }
    }

    protected void onUpdate(@Nonnull T newValue) {
        // Override in subclasses for side effects
    }

    @Nonnull
    public T getValue() {
        return value != null ? value : defaultValue;
    }

    @Nonnull
    public String getKey() {
        return key;
    }
}
```

**Subclasses to create:**

```java
// IntRangeSetting - for health, damage, etc.
public class IntRangeSetting extends ItemSetting<Integer> {
    private final int min;
    private final int max;

    public IntRangeSetting(String key, int defaultValue, int min, int max) {
        super(key, defaultValue);
        this.min = min;
        this.max = max;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean validateInput(Integer input) {
        return input >= min && input <= max;
    }
}

// EnumSetting - for item types, etc.
public class EnumSetting<E extends Enum<E>> extends ItemSetting<E> {
    private final Class<E> enumType;

    public EnumSetting(String key, E defaultValue, Class<E> enumType) {
        super(key, defaultValue);
        this.enumType = enumType;
    }
}
```

**Time: 6-8 hours**

